  "doc_id": "33070",
  "text": "GPI-AP deficient granulocytes, T lymphocytes, and RBCs were analyzed by flow cytometry using specific monoclonal antibody cocktails: fluorescent aerolysin reagent (FLAER)-Ax488/CD24-PE for granulocytes, FLAER-Ax488/CD3-PE for T lymphocytes, and CD55-FITC/CD59-PE for RBCs. The FLAER-based flow-cytometric assay is recommended to screen for GPI-AP deficient white blood cells (WBCs) because it has higher sensitivity than that based on other GPI-APs, including CD55, CD59, CD24, and CD14, and can detect small clone sizes in PNH as well as AA or myelodysplastic syndrome [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] .",
